svg.title: Reflections on My Study of Confucianism as a Religion

g.title: 1. 25 April, conference of Prof. Huang Chin-shing, Vice-President of the Academia Sinica. 2. The Cult of Confucius and the Imperial System of Rites. 3. Confucian Ethic and Economic Development: Myth or Fact?

Discussing whether Confucianism is called a religion has become a hot topic in recent years. However, this issue is endless debate and difficult to conclude since the late Qing Dynasty. Professor Huang Chin- Shing try to review the fact that Confucianism is a religious from a methodological point of view. This approach focuses on the interaction the sacred space with believer. Compared with other historical religions, "Analects of Confucius" is roundabout so that it is difficult to demonstrate its religious character.
